platformAttributes.ios.editorialNotes.st.k: The makers of the awesomely chaotic Does Not Commute have returned with a very different sort of game, casting you as a lab tech who must recapture subatomic particles as they drift away from an atomic core. Connecting coloured dots might sound simple enough, but every neuron in your decidedly non-mechanical brain will be firing as you extend your particle strings and snag valuable score multipliers. Soothing ambient music perfectly complements the intense focus required to master each rewarding level. Who said lab work was boring?
